<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-06-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-06-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="51" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d51">
                    <head>No. 51.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Putnam</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Blaine</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Brussels</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-06-13"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 13, 1881</date>.
                            (Received June 25.)</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 72.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge receipt of
                        dispatch No. 45, and to state that I have in person, and by note, expressed
                        to the minister <pb facs="0197" n="73" xml:id="pg_73"/> of foreign affairs
                        the satisfaction with which the Government of the United States has learned
                        the action of the Belgian Government relating to the importation and use of
                        American pork.</p>
                    <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                    <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>JAMES O. PUTNAM.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>